title: rustc segfaults on stable
body:
I tried this code: ```rust use serde::{Deserializer, Deserialize}; pub struct Foo; impl<'a> Deserialize<'a> for Foo { fn deserialize>(_: D) -> Result { #[derive(Deserialize)] enum Field { Format } Ok(Foo) } } fn main() { } ``` I expected for it to compile, but stable rustc segfaults. This is not the case for the latest nightly rustc. [Relevant playground link](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=d1b47e089fbd16d7d4f83c72c9a14c88). ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.55.0 (c8dfcfe04 2021-09-06) binary: rustc commit-hash: c8dfcfe046a7680554bf4eb612bad840e7631c4b commit-date: 2021-09-06 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.55.0 LLVM version: 12.0.1 ```
